# TypeScript Frontend Rules

## Structure
- `src/lib/` — emulator-api, types, utilities
- `src/components/` — feature components; `components/ui/` for shadcn
- All backend calls via `EmulatorAPI` in `emulator-api.ts`

## Style
- Functional components + hooks
- No `any`; types for all Tauri responses from `emulator-types.ts`
- Side effects in hooks, not in render
- JSDoc for non-trivial components

## Adding UI
- Use shadcn: `npx shadcn@latest add [component]`
- New components in `src/components/` or `src/components/ui/`
- Style with Tailwind; prefer composition over prop drilling

## Avoid
- Bypassing `EmulatorAPI`
- Logic in components — use hooks or API layer
- Extra npm deps — prefer Radix/Lucide/shadcn
- Overly complex components — split them
